Doctors and nurses have not been reporting for duty citing incapacitation, as their salaries can no longer sustain them. Apart from demands for better salaries, Zimbabwean doctors have also been calling on government, to provide sundry required in all major referral hospitals. 
Currently doctors are earning less that $100 per months, the lowest in the region. 

Channel Africa's Simon Muchemwa has more from Harare...

